transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, how can I help you today?

Speaker 1: Got it.

Speaker 1: Hold on.

Speaker 2: Hello?

Speaker 1: Hello, sir.

Speaker 2: Can I get your zip code and your last name, please, in order?

Speaker 1: Not in order.

Speaker 2: Candidate and 34788.

Speaker 1: What's the zip code?

Speaker 2: Yeah, 34788.

Speaker 1: And your first name?

Speaker 2: Bobby.

Speaker 1: Got it.

Speaker 2: All right, so I'm not sure.

Speaker 1: Basically, let me see here.

Speaker 2: So, yes, every order in the AG Viagra needs to be on a refill date to be shipped out.

Speaker 1: It doesn't mean you need to get the refill.

Speaker 2: Hold on.

Speaker 1: Explain that to her for me, okay?

Speaker 2: I need to talk to the patient.

Speaker 1: You can have it on the speaker, though, but I do need to make sure you're on the phone.

Speaker 2: Hold on.

Speaker 1: Say it again now.

Speaker 2: Yes, so every order of the AG Viagra requires a refill date to become active.

Speaker 1: You don't need to take the second order.

Speaker 2: You just need to have a refill date.

Speaker 1: In this case, what I could do for you guys to make sure this is properly sent out and delivered,

Speaker 2: I could just freeze it out for six months.

Speaker 1: Try it out.

Speaker 2: Once you receive the AG Viagra, try it out and give us a call back.

Speaker 1: Let us know if you want to keep it or change the frequency or if you decide to just stop all orders

Speaker 2: because that would eliminate the visit and you won't be able to order it.

Speaker 1: But at least for the first order to be shipped out, it does require the date.

Speaker 2: Well, I don't want it six months.

Speaker 1: I just wanted, like, one pill.

Speaker 2: I don't want to keep it that long.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I'm not sure if you were able to just hear what I said.

Speaker 2: I explained quite a lot right now.

Speaker 1: It needs to have a refill date to be shipped out.

Speaker 2: Even if you want just one, it needs a refill date to be shipped out.

Speaker 1: But you could call us afterwards even to make any modifications.

Speaker 2: I don't want it on my thing.

Speaker 1: I don't want no prescription.

Speaker 2: I don't want to wait six months.

Speaker 1: I want it off.

Speaker 2: No, did you?

Speaker 1: Were you?

Speaker 2: I'm not sure if you're hearing me, sir, because what part are you missing right here?

Speaker 1: I'm not telling you you need to wait six months.

Speaker 2: What part were you not understanding?

Speaker 1: I just want to help better understand.

Speaker 2: Because I know how it works, because they'll bill you for it when you don't want it.

Speaker 1: No, I just explained to you, sir, the order needs to have a refill date to be sent out and delivered.

Speaker 2: Without the refill date, the order cannot be sent out and delivered.

Speaker 1: Hasn't it been shipped already?

Speaker 2: No, it hasn't.

Speaker 1: It's still at the USPS waiting for a label, I believe.

Speaker 2: However, what I'm trying to tell you is I'm going to freeze it for six months so you don't receive an order.

Speaker 1: However, when you get your order, call us back and make the final decision there if you want to just cancel it entirely

Speaker 2: or if you want to adjust your frequency.

Speaker 1: Okay, so I can do that as soon as I get the prescription in the mail.

Speaker 2: Exactly.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right, then I'll call you back when I get it done.

Speaker 1: Yeah, no problem.

Speaker 2: Call us back.

Speaker 1: That way you can receive your first order.

Speaker 2: But then let us know what the final choice will be based on once you get your order, basically.

Speaker 1: But you said that it was sitting waiting to be shipped.

Speaker 2: They sent me a message.

Speaker 1: It's at the USPS with the label right now.

Speaker 2: I know, but they sent me one on my phone and said it was already shipped.

Speaker 1: Yeah, they sent you the tracking number, sir.

Speaker 2: That doesn't mean the package is shipped out from the facility.

Speaker 1: Okay, and there's no way to stop it even though it ain't been mailed yet?

Speaker 2: Correct, because it's been approved and sent out through the doctor.

Speaker 1: All you have to do is call us back once you get your order.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: No problem.

Speaker 1: Have a good one.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye.
